1'><teachingTypeInCurriculum><typeOfTeaching>theory</typeOfTeaching><percentage>15</percentage></teachingTypeInCurriculum><teachingTypeInCurriculum><typeOfTeaching>practice</typeOfTeaching><percentage>45</percentage></teachingTypeInCurriculum><teachingTypeInCurriculum><typeOfTeaching>self study</typeOfTeaching><percentage>40</percentage></teachingTypeInCurriculum></teachingTypesInCurriculumYear></programCurriculum><programDescriptions><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>tuition fee</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[There’s a great need for good programmers in both the commercial sector and the field of research. The programme will help you become a better programmer and understand every aspect of the software engineering process. You learn how to reflect and analyse situations, which allows you to objectively assess both your own work and that of others. Graduates are therefore highly sought after on the labour market and tend to move up the career ladder quite quickly.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>job perspective</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Software Engineering onderscheid zich van klassieke computer science-opleidingen door onzekerheid over de impact van ontwerpkeuzes. Wat goed is voor de performance, heeft ook invloed op de onderhoudbaarheid en complexiteit. Als software engineer en onderzoeker proberen we grip te krijgen op deze wisselwerking en afhankelijkheden te verminderen. Omdat de context van een applicatie dynamisch is en er sprake is van tegengestelde belangen van stakeholders is er niet één beste oplossing.

De technieken en design patterns die we hebben ontwikkeld passen vaak niet goed op de problemen. Net als een onderzoeker leren we jou om een goede probleemanalyse te doen; om een idee te vormen over de oplossing en om te toetsen of je ideeën kloppen.

We besteden daarnaast veel aandacht aan de menselijke kant van software engineering. Dit speelt een grote rol bij het formuleren van eisen, het gebruik van software, maar ook bij effectiviteit van het team en kwaliteit van de software.]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="de"><![CDATA[Software Engineering is a programme about methods and process of software development.

It will be taught in English from September 2011.]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Over the course of this Master's degree programme, you will become familiar with every aspect of the broad and dynamic field of software engineering. We are seeking students with a Bachelor's degree from a university of applied sciences or research university that are motivated to learn more about this multifaceted profession. 

You are eager to learn and interested in tackling challenges for which there is no standard solution. You would like to acquire the necessary skills in order to complete complex software projects. How does one determine and interpret the needs of a client seeking to purchase or develop a new software system? How can you learn to recognise, resolve and prevent defects in a software system? How can theoretical knowledge and professional literature be applied in practice?]]></programDescription><programName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Software Engineering]]></programName><programName xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Software Engineering]]></programName><programSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Grote softwareprojecten zijn complex; standaardoplossingen voldoen niet. Deze éénjarige master maakt van jou een betere engineer en ontwerper, zodat je grote projecten tot een succes kan brengen.]]></programSummary><programSummary xml:lang="de"><![CDATA[Software Engineering is a programme in English about methods and process of software development.]]></programSummary><programSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Software Engineering is a programme about methods and processes of software development.]]></programSummary><searchword xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[process]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[computers]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[engineering]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[ICT]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[information engineering]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[programmeren]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[software]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[internet]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[automatisering]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[beta]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[digitalisering]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[techniek]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[ontwerpen]]></searchword><search